                        <div class="title">
                          <a href="/topics/18610" title="Is there an AR association to do this??">Is there an AR association to do this?</a>    
                        </div>
                        <div class="media-body">
                        <p>
								                  I have an equipment model and a technician model:<br></br>
                  class Device < ActiveRecord::Base<br></br>
                    attr_accessible :name, :technician_id, :backup_tech_id<br></br>
                    belongs_to :technician<br></br>
                  end<br></br>
                  class Technician < ActiveRecord::Base<br></br>
                    attr_accessible :name<br></br>
                    has_many :devices<br></br>
                  end<br></br>
                  Each Device has to have a primary technician and a backup technician. Obviously it wouldn't make sense to create a separate "BackupTech" model so my question is, is there some AR association voodoo that will let me use a Technician as a "BackupTech"?
                   
                  Thanks.
					 </p>
		                  </div>
                        <div class="info">
